                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17241014-17-off84 t17241014-17-cd85"></join> last, and Pritchard and Risdel for being aiding and abetting
            </rs>. They were indicted a second Time upon the Coroner's Inquest: And a third Time for the Murder of Samuel Orchard, there being no Weapon drawn. The Witnesses for the King were, 
               <persName id="t17241014-17-person96">
                  Thomas 
                  Dillo 
